eir intimate view of how people understand ethnicity, locality, the body, and nature. This ethnography of knowledge diversities in multiethnic China is a testament to the rural wisdom of mountain healers, one that theorizes, from the ground up, the dynamic encounters between formal statist knowledge and the popular authority of the wild.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHealerszChina, Southeast. 0aMedicinal plantszChina, Southeast. 0aMedicine, ChinesezChina, Southeast. 0aYao (Southeast Asian people)xMedicine. 0aZhuang (Chinese people)xMedicine. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aanthropology of the state.  aembodiment.  agathering.  ainstitution.  aknowledge.  aminority nationalities.  aplants.  atraditional medicines.1 aLai, Lili, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226763798423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226763798/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DSLb2021